               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1847">Internally dated to the year <foreign xml:lang="ta">pārapava</foreign> of the Jovian cycle, that is, either  <foreign xml:lang="ta">pirapava</foreign>, that is CE 1807-1808, 1747-1748, 1687-1688, etc., or  <foreign xml:lang="ta">parapāva</foreign>, that is, CE 1846-1847, 1786-1787, 1726-1727, etc. See colophon (U2, f145v2). Dated to circa 1747 by Vinson in Vinson et al. (1866-), on the basis of the internal date, and to 1747 by Cabaton (1912), on unstated grounds (presumably palaeographical and material analysis arguments).</origDate>
                     <origPlace>Pondicherry.</origPlace>
                  </origin>
